node.text: @alisoneroman knew the internet would yell at her about the Thousand Island Dressing. But she is a bold and brave woman who doesn't want a mixture of mayo + ketchup on her crunchy, citrusy seafood salad, so here we are. If you make this, you won't be mad about it. Get the recipe here: https://nyti.ms/2WWluna (Video: @scottloitsch @vaughn)

node.title: Alison Roman Makes New Shrimp Louie

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 30, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: This orzo dish from @thisiskaychun has all the goods: feta, tomatoes, bell peppers and herbs. Recipe link in bio! (Photo: @linda.xiao, food styling: @monicapierini)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 30, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: It's Monday. Here's @itsalislagle's Cinnamon Toast. Recipe link in bio! (Photo: @lindaxiao, food styling: @rebeccajurkevich)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 29, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Great Sunday night idea: Whip up @samanthaseneviratne's Cheesecake-Chocolate Pudding Bars and make Monday a lot less... Monday. Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @bryangardnerphotography, food styling: @bwashbu)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 29, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Grating a tomato somehow brings out everything that's delicious about it. Get @tejalxrao's recipe for Paneer con Tomate at the link in bio. (Photo: @linda.xiao, food styling: @heysueli, prop styling: @nicolelouie)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 29, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Sarah in the comments section calls @thisiskaychun's Sweet Corn and Scallop Pasta "summer magic." ✨ Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @bryangardnerphotography, food styling: @bwashbu)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 29, 2021. May be an image of food.

node.text: Keep the summer vibes alive with @david_tanis's Melon, Cucumber and Cherry Tomato Salad. 🍈🥒🍅 Recipe at the link in bio! (Photo: @dmalosh, food styling: @simoncooks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 28, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Haven't eaten dinner yet? Grab some avocados and make @la_yoselin's Avocado Soup With Chile Oil with the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @chrisrsimpson, food styling: @simoncooks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 28, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: @la_yoselin's Mushroom Chicharrón Tacos are about to become your new go-to vegetarian taco recipe. Make them with the link in bio! (Photo: @linda.xiao, food styling: @hadassmirnoff)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 28, 2021. May be an image of burger.

node.text: "10/10 would make again; in fact I may have to update my default technique." @kenjilopezalt's Thin but Juicy Chargrilled Burgers will have you rethinking everything you know about burgers. Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @bryangardnerphotography, food styling: @bwashbu)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 28, 2021. May be an image of dessert.

node.text: Making @dawnkperry's Blackberry Frozen Yogurt Pie With Cracker Crust is a great way to show someone you like them a lot. Get the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @dmalosh, food styling: @simoncooks)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by NYT Cooking on August 27, 2021. May be an image of chicken sandwich and club sandwich.

node.text: @yewande_komolafe's Muhammara Chicken Sandwiches are picnic-perfect. Pack your blankets and baskets, and make them with the recipe at the link in bio. (Photo: @linda.xiao, food styling: @monicapierini)
